This is the value of all High Quality Liquid Assets as determined in accordance with the relevant prudential standards, net of the value of adjusted HQLA Deposit Liabilities.
Adjusted HQLA Deposit Liabilities are High Quality Liquid Asset deposits held by the reporting party as at the relevant date, and which are capable of being redeemed or withdrawn by depositors from the reporting party within 2 business days, with or without penalty. The value of Adjusted HQLA Deposit Liabilities is limited to the value of HQLA Deposit Assets, which are the High Quality Liquid Asset deposits at the relevant date redeemable or withdrawable by the reporting party on demand or within 2 business days. The net value is determined by reducing the deposit amount by any break costs or early withdrawal penalties that would be applied for redeeming the deposit within 2 business days.

This balancing item represents total derivative contracts less those contracts which are classed as any of the following: - Interest rate contracts; - Foreign exchange contracts; - Gold contracts; - Precious metals contracts; or - Equity contracts.
Derivatives are generally defined as those instruments/contracts, where the value is based on other products, and/or on prices associated with financial products. Derivative contracts involve: - Future delivery, receipt or exchange of financial items such as cash or another derivative instrument; or - Future exchange of real assets for financial items where the contract may be tradeable and has a market value. The contracts can either be binding on both parties (e.g. as with a currency swap) or subject to the exercise by one party of a right contained within the contract (as with options).
Report this item regardless of whether favourable or unfavourable to the reporting entity.
Assets Other Financial Assets Derivative Contracts Other Amount
